The new species is distinguished from other species by male with the median apophysis (M) triangular, with marginal long and thick teeth (
Figure 25I
).

Palpal coxae 0.41 long, 0.22 wide. Palpal measurements (femur + patella + tibia + tarsus = total): 0.55 + 0.19 + 0.31 + 0.44 = 1.50; the length of tibia 1.60 times that of patella. Palpal tibia with three dorsal trichobothria (
Figure 23A,B
); TBS thick, bend at apical part (
Figure 23B
). Tarsus dwindles distally, with relatively shallow AC in middle part, RA in adjacent apical part in retrolateral view; retrolateral side with row of short setae on RA and at mid-tarsus; a group long setae at apical part (
Figure 23A,B
). Bulb suboval, PL shuttle-shaped (
Figure 23A
); M triangular, gradient, with six thick and long marginal teeth, (
Figure 25I
); PF transparent, willow-leaf shaped (
Figure 23A,B
).

Abdomen pale yellow, with a few purple-brown markings, sparse hair, 1.07 long, 0.77 wide (
Figure 24A
).

Female 
paratype
.

Total length 2.40. Carapace smooth, 0.87 long, 0.77 wide, height at fovea 0.73 times carapace width, yellowish; thoracic fovea brown, needle-shaped (
Figure 24D
). Clypeus 0.49 high, yellowish. Chelicerae 0.49 long, yellowish, with six teeth and two denticles on promargin of fang furrow and five denticles on retromargin; seven short setae on base (
Figure 23D
). Six eyes; ocular area 0.10 long, 0.21 wide; anterior row strongly recurved, ALE 0.06, PLE 0.06, PLE–PLE 0.09; PME 0.05, slightly smaller than anterior row of eyes, contiguous; dark pigment between eyes (
Figure 24D
). Sternum 0.58 long, 0.55 wide, haired; labium 0.08 long, 0.17 wide, yellowish.

Abdomen similar to male, 1.58 long, 1.17 wide. Epigynal plate broadly rugby-ballshaped, simple (
Figure 23E
); internal genitalia with a pair of spermathecae, coiled sperm duct, fan-shaped atrium (
Figure 23F
).
